  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Multidrug resistance bacteria infection is common in ICU. Infection incidence is associated
      with age, organ dysfunction, invasive treatment and enviroment cleaning. According to
      hospital hygienic standard for disinfection, total numbers of colony of air and the object
      surface in ICU must be ≤4CFU/cm2（5min）and≤10CFU/cm2. in this study, the two different methods
      will be used to evaluate the disinfection effects in ICU enviroments.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
